It’s our viability week🌈🤍 Viability week in medicine is the point at which a fetus can survive outside the womb. It is generally considered to be around 23 or 24 weeks. This is a huge milestone for women who’ve experienced miscarriages because knowing if you go into early labor, your baby has a 70% chance of survival. I’ll be honest at the time of this shoot I was still struggling with embracing my pregnancy fully, to put it plainly I was excited but still fearful. I prayed to God to make it this far! So here we are, 24 weeks, almost to the finish line. God has blown my mind, I am grateful. God has restored what I lost, and has proven to me he keeps his promises. He simply doesn’t renege. 

🤍 Keep growing and kicking mommy baby girl! #viablilityweek #girlmom
